how I got here.

00:24.372 --> 00:26.852
Franco: They were headed to
the airport, boarding a plane.

00:26.896 --> 00:29.768
Mitch: So, where's Rinaldo?
He's in Cuba?

00:29.812 --> 00:33.163
They flew to, you know,
parts unknown, offshore.

00:33.207 --> 00:35.513
You should see the footage--

00:35.557 --> 00:38.603
hookers, bottle service,
you name it.

00:38.647 --> 00:40.910
He could be a dangerous man.

00:40.953 --> 00:42.520
Mike:
About our money here,

00:42.564 --> 00:44.131
the people that I deal with,
they're a bunch of mugs.

00:44.174 --> 00:45.958
These guys want
their money back.

00:46.002 --> 00:47.351
They feel they're getting
bamboozled all over the place,

00:47.395 --> 00:49.136
right, and they don't
like doing that.

00:49.179 --> 00:51.268
- Uh, no problem.
- Mike: It's not a problem?

00:51.312 --> 00:53.096
- It's not a problem
to me, my friend.

00:53.140 --> 00:54.837
So, why don't you tell me how
we're gonna get our money back?

00:54.880 --> 00:57.144
At Harvard, we learn about
how to be a bull-shitter,

00:57.187 --> 00:58.406
how to Harvard-bullshit.

00:58.449 --> 01:00.147
You know, it's like a course.

01:00.190 --> 01:02.584
So, let's hope your "trust me"
is a guaranteed "trust me"

01:02.627 --> 01:04.281
'cause I've heard it
a million times before.

01:04.325 --> 01:06.283
Okay, don't trust me,
but I'm not going anywhere.

01:06.327 --> 01:08.024
- Mike: Thank you.
- Mitch: Okay.

01:08.068 --> 01:09.504
Mike: I'm going to take you
as a man of your word.

01:09.547 --> 01:11.375
Franco: Who's funding
this guy's fantasy life?

01:11.419 --> 01:12.985
Did you give him any money?

01:13.029 --> 01:15.423
Rinaldo wants to do his project,
wherever that is.

01:15.466 --> 01:19.296
I'm running through the books as
we're investing in his project.

01:19.340 --> 01:22.125
I'm getting out of the country

01:22.169 --> 01:24.171
and I have some time

01:24.214 --> 01:26.869
to get to know his
beautiful wife, Julianne.

01:26.912 --> 01:30.525
Well, here I was thinking
I was in control.

01:35.051 --> 01:37.532
As you know,
it's a crumbling house of cards.

01:37.575 --> 01:40.317
I think our time is done here.

01:40.361 --> 01:43.668
Just be calm.
Pretend everything's all right.

01:43.712 --> 01:46.628
If, um-- if they start
seizing the equipment,

01:46.671 --> 01:50.762
just tell 'em we don't own it.
It's leased. They can't have it.

01:50.806 --> 01:53.156
So, we better,
like, move quickly.

01:53.200 --> 01:55.724
And I see the backstairs,
so let's move quickly.

01:55.767 --> 01:58.074
You should go,
and I'll talk to Doreen.

01:58.118 --> 01:59.554
I'll make sure
she gets out of here.

01:59.597 --> 02:01.164
Doreen? Doreen?

02:01.208 --> 02:02.426
[knocking]

02:02.470 --> 02:03.819
[whispering] You got to go.

02:03.862 --> 02:05.342
They're coming for us.
You got to go.

02:05.386 --> 02:06.909
Yeah, yeah. We got to go.

02:06.952 --> 02:08.824
I would go immediately
down the staircase.

02:08.866 --> 02:12.393
I'll bring my car around and
I'll see you in the alleyway.

02:12.436 --> 02:15.265
Put the equipment in my car
and we'll keep moving.

02:15.309 --> 02:18.964
Okay. Don't look back.
We're good.

02:22.490 --> 02:25.014
Could you help me
take the sign off, actually?

02:25.057 --> 02:27.277
We don't have time.
I got to go. I got to go, guys.

02:27.321 --> 02:29.584
Well, I thought
I was in control.

02:29.627 --> 02:31.194
I thought I was the king.

02:31.238 --> 02:33.849
I thought I was
running a studio;

02:33.892 --> 02:36.765
hiring, firing, making
decisions, getting money,

02:36.808 --> 02:39.159
handing money out.

02:42.597 --> 02:52.607
♪

03:20.156 --> 03:22.463
So, guys,
slight little wrinkle.

03:22.506 --> 03:24.421
