come in as I'd like

03:24.465 --> 03:25.901
and our lease was up,

03:25.944 --> 03:27.468
and they were taking
some of our stuff.

03:27.511 --> 03:30.993
So, I thought we'd, um,
be on the move a little bit.

03:31.036 --> 03:34.866
We're gonna, you know, try to
pull together this season

03:34.910 --> 03:37.826
in sort of a really--
how would I put it?

03:37.869 --> 03:40.655
Low-cost,
but very cost-effective way.

03:40.698 --> 03:43.353
You know, we have
some really great actors that,

03:43.397 --> 03:45.137
you know, I've e-mailed out,

03:45.181 --> 03:46.965
and hopefully
will be joining us.

03:47.009 --> 03:50.795
And I think back and probably
my closest relationship

03:50.839 --> 03:53.407
throughout this whole project
was with Franco.

03:55.060 --> 03:58.107
So, I have an idea.

03:58.150 --> 04:00.501
I'm going to call Franco.

04:02.764 --> 04:04.113
I liked him,
I didn't like him.

04:04.156 --> 04:05.636
We're friends,
we're not friends.

04:05.680 --> 04:07.986
He relied up on me,
I relied upon him.

04:08.030 --> 04:09.771
We're not in our old studio,

04:09.814 --> 04:11.338
