20:09.512 --> 20:11.035
♪ I like it like that

20:11.079 --> 20:13.560
You know that song?
I love it, man.

20:13.603 --> 20:16.563
Listen. I'm going to
teach you something, okay?

20:16.606 --> 20:19.522
These are little step-by-step.

20:19.566 --> 20:22.873
I'm going to give a break
to these beautiful girls.

20:22.917 --> 20:24.527
They're going to freshen up
for me.

20:24.571 --> 20:27.095
Look at this toe.

20:27.138 --> 20:29.967
See? Gentle, nice.

20:30.011 --> 20:33.275
Look at the other one.
Look at this. See?

20:33.319 --> 20:35.799
One day, you're going to
get there, like me, man.

20:35.843 --> 20:39.020
Look at that.

20:39.063 --> 20:42.241
Just get the-- you know,
the tap, a bubble bath.

20:42.284 --> 20:45.766
In the meantime,
you can go ahead, okay?

20:55.166 --> 20:58.082
Malik:
Don Punta, here's Mitch.

20:58.126 --> 20:59.345
Rinaldo!

20:59.388 --> 21:00.607
Rinaldo:
Hey, Mitch.

21:00.650 --> 21:02.391
How are you, man?

21:02.435 --> 21:04.437
Rinaldo, my friend...

21:04.480 --> 21:05.916
Yeah? Speak up, man.

21:05.960 --> 21:07.222
Speak up?

21:07.266 --> 21:09.006
Yeah. What's your concern?

21:09.050 --> 21:12.401
My concern.
Remember I gave you $250,000?

21:12.445 --> 21:14.185
You came to me, to my office.

21:14.229 --> 21:16.013
You said you're an actor

21:16.057 --> 21:19.887
and you had a dream to do
a film called Punta Brothers.

21:19.930 --> 21:21.454
- Right.
- And...

21:21.497 --> 21:22.716
Yeah, and?

21:22.759 --> 21:24.500
It seems to be in trouble.

21:24.544 --> 21:26.197
What's going on?
Tell me what happened to--

21:26.241 --> 21:28.374
Trouble? See, that word
"trouble," I don't like it, man.

21:28.417 --> 21:31.899
"Trouble,"
it's out of my vocabulary.

21:31.942 --> 21:35.294
Malik come fresh. This guy...

21:35.337 --> 21:36.991
Mitch:
Malik come fresh?

21:37.034 --> 21:40.081
Malik is, uh-- he's my host.
He has no acting ability.

21:40.124 --> 21:43.911
Hey, I already talked to him.
He's taking care of it.

21:43.954 --> 21:45.216
What are you doing? Like...

21:45.260 --> 21:46.827
You fucked my wife.

21:46.870 --> 21:48.219
What does that have
to do with anything?

21:48.263 --> 21:49.699
Hey, you know what?

21:49.743 --> 21:51.310
- You owe me.
- Why do I owe you?

21:51.353 --> 21:53.355
Remember, you came to me, idiot.

21:53.399 --> 21:56.576
You came to me, said,
"I need you to help out my wife.

21:56.619 --> 21:58.360
She has a problem
with the immigration."

21:58.404 --> 22:00.536
I said I'll help her out,
and in order to help her out,

22:00.580 --> 22:02.233
she had to become my fake wife.

22:02.277 --> 22:05.062
I just experienced
a come-to-Jesus moment.

22:05.106 --> 22:08.718
So, what are you blaming me for?
I loved her.

22:08.762 --> 22:10.372
You didn't love her.
I wanted her,

22:10.416 --> 22:12.809
and she ended up sleeping
with everybody else.

22:12.853 --> 22:14.289
You owe me, man!

22:14.333 --> 22:15.377
No. You owe me, man.

22:15.421 --> 22:16.770
You owe me.

22:16.813 --> 22:19.990
Mitch:
I want to take down Rinaldo

22:20.034 --> 22:22.602
and I want to walk off
into the sunset.

22:46.626 --> 22:49.455
Rinaldo, you look
a little hung over there, man.

22:49.498 --> 22:52.022
Oh, yeah. You know, things.

22:52.066 --> 22:54.373
Uh, I gave him $250,000.

22:54.416 --> 22:57.332
He promised me a screenplay.

22:57.376 --> 22:58.551
It was called
the Punta Brothers.

22:58.594 --> 22:59.987
You're not well?

23:00.030 --> 23:01.597
If you're not well,
we'll get you a doctor.

23:01.641 --> 23:04.078
I have no idea what's going on.
I mean, what happened?

23:04.121 --> 23:06.385
It's a stomach flu? Is it
intestinal flu? What's going on?

23:06.428 --> 23:07.777
Rinaldo:
Your man's still alive,

23:07.821 --> 23:09.213
so that's what matters, right?

23:09.257 --> 23:12.434
Rinaldo, we have
a large investment in you.

23:12.478 --> 23:15.263
Maybe there's a novel
out of this.

23:15.306 --> 23:16.569
Maybe if it's a great
screenplay,

23:16.612 --> 23:17.961
we could novelize it.

23:18.005 --> 23:20.050
They don't have
cocaine here in Cuba, man.

23:20.094 --> 23:21.704
It's not a big thing here.

23:21.748 --> 23:24.054
A screenplay leads to a novel,
maybe leads to a play.

23:24.098 --> 23:25.447
Maybe do a Broadway play.

23:25.491 --> 23:27.362
There's all kinds
of possibilities.

23:27.406 --> 23:28.581
Or maybe a TV series.

23:28.624 --> 23:31.105
Goran, Rinaldo? Let's sit down.

23:31.148 --> 23:33.063
Goran:
He's got some kind of script

23:33.107 --> 23:35.239
that I have to shoot.

23:35.283 --> 23:37.328
He's never written
anything before,

23:37.372 --> 23:41.855
so that's really
a confidence-builder.

23:41.898 --> 23:43.900
He's a great director,
but he used to be an actor.

23:43.944 --> 23:45.162
Now, he's a director.

23:45.206 --> 23:46.686
So he'll be both
a director and an actor.

23:46.729 --> 23:48.339
It's like a combo.

23:48.383 --> 23:49.732
Mitch: So, Goran should be
an interesting guy.

23:49.776 --> 23:51.168
I've heard
some wonderful things about him.

23:51.212 --> 23:53.388
He was a big star
in the '70s and '80s,

23:53.432 --> 23:55.129
an action figure.

23:55.172 --> 23:57.697
- So, the guy is good, eh?
- Mitch: He's really good.

23:57.740 --> 24:00.134
Played with a lot of
the major players in Hollywood,

24:00.177 --> 24:03.572
and now, he's transformed
himself into a director.

24:03.616 --> 24:06.488
Let me look at this guy, man.
He's kind of...

24:06.532 --> 24:09.970
The eye is
the window to the souls.

24:10.013 --> 24:11.885
Goran: With this production,
it's always the same thing.

24:11.928 --> 24:13.756
I get there. It's a nightmare.

24:13.800 --> 24:16.846
Yeah. I can see
some potential in this guy.

24:16.890 --> 24:18.195
I like him.

24:18.239 --> 24:19.458
Goran: You know, no one listens.

24:19.501 --> 24:22.025
That's not how you direct, man.

24:22.069 --> 24:24.071
Gracias, señora.

24:25.420 --> 24:28.162
Nice box. Hey.

24:28.205 --> 24:30.033
Okay, amigos.

24:30.077 --> 24:31.905
We going to celebrate
the new chapter

24:31.948 --> 24:33.167
in the Punta Brothers.

24:33.210 --> 24:34.690
- Salud.
- Salud.

24:34.734 --> 24:36.387
- Goran: Salud, guys.
- Salud. Salud.

24:36.431 --> 24:39.086
They think I'm stupid,
but I know what I'm doing here.

24:45.135 --> 24:47.094
Rinaldo: I'm still in
a hangover type of thing.

24:47.137 --> 24:49.836
You know,
that wasn't really me.

24:49.879 --> 24:52.360
I'm serious about this project.

24:52.403 --> 24:53.579
Mitch: Rinaldo has a passion
for what he's doing,

24:53.622 --> 24:54.928
but if it doesn't work out,

24:54.971 --> 24:56.843
then maybe
I'll do my own screenplay.

24:56.886 --> 24:58.975
Maybe I'll
take over the acting,

24:59.019 --> 25:00.716
because I really love
the acting.

25:00.760 --> 25:03.153
Goran: It's going to take me
hours to get to location.

25:03.197 --> 25:04.415
I don't know where they are,

25:04.459 --> 25:07.549
and I'm in no hurry,
like I told you.

25:07.593 --> 25:11.118
And I'm dreading it, frankly.
These people are out of control.

25:11.161 --> 25:13.424
The last couple of times

25:13.468 --> 25:16.993
I tried to direct
with these people,

25:17.037 --> 25:18.560
it was a nightmare.

25:18.604 --> 25:20.954
I almost changed profession.

25:22.912 --> 25:24.914
You know, this is
always a mystery to me.

25:38.928 --> 25:41.148
Mitch: I went by
the villa, and no one's there.

25:41.191 --> 25:43.411
Can't get in.

25:43.454 --> 25:45.935
So, I thought I'd just go to
a local cafeteria,

25:45.979 --> 25:48.416
N + A Cafeteria
around the corner,

25:48.459 --> 25:51.854
just to get in
Cuban sort of culture.

25:51.898 --> 25:54.117
And again, it's a great
opportunity to write,

25:54.161 --> 25:56.119
and I'm excited.

25:58.121 --> 25:59.558
Goran: You know, these
guys are a little better

25:59.601 --> 26:00.776
than the last batch.

26:00.820 --> 26:04.432
Rinaldo, he's a natural.

26:04.475 --> 26:07.478
If I had a restaurant,
he'd be working in my kitchen.

26:08.654 --> 26:11.178
Rinaldo:
Don Punta is my idea, man.

26:11.221 --> 26:14.007
If nobody agree with that,
fuck it.

26:14.050 --> 26:17.967
If they don't like the script,
I rip the whole thing.

26:18.011 --> 26:20.491
I use it for toilet paper.
So what?

26:20.535 --> 26:22.972
Fuck.

26:25.671 --> 26:27.977
Mitch:
This reminds me of Hemingway,

26:28.021 --> 26:29.283
his classic book
I read in high school,

26:29.326 --> 26:30.763
Old Man and the Sea.

26:30.806 --> 26:33.417
No jokes here, guys.
I still feel young.

26:33.461 --> 26:36.116
Wow.

26:49.912 --> 26:53.089
Goran: If you look at
the sequence of events,

26:53.133 --> 26:56.832
I show up
for a production meeting,

26:56.876 --> 26:58.181
and this guy's got

26:58.225 --> 27:00.793
women all over the place,
dancing.

27:00.836 --> 27:05.014
And I'm fully expecting
maybe a staff meeting.

27:05.058 --> 27:07.669
Instead, I've got these
beautiful women dancing around.

27:07.713 --> 27:10.890
I mean,
it was really bizarre.

27:10.933 --> 27:13.327
You know, I was assured
maybe this time it'll work.

27:13.370 --> 27:14.720
It'll be more professional.

27:16.112 --> 27:18.419
Mitch? He's something else, too.

27:18.462 --> 27:22.553
I mean, he's supposed
to be, like, an executive.

27:22.597 --> 27:24.686
He was very serious,
but soon as he saw the girls,

27:24.730 --> 27:27.036
he totally abandoned me.

27:27.080 --> 27:30.779
He's originally
a hotshot lawyer,

27:30.823 --> 27:32.825
and he's right in there
in the thick of things,

27:32.868 --> 27:34.391
dancing like--

27:34.435 --> 27:36.611
He's a pretty good dancer,
actually.

27:36.655 --> 27:38.091
It's unbelievable.

27:38.134 --> 27:39.745
I've never seen anything
like it, but you know,

27:39.788 --> 27:42.443
now, I can say I've
seen everything in production.

27:45.533 --> 27:47.622
I'm going to say, yeah,
that guy Don Punta,

27:47.666 --> 27:50.843
he's a real loose cannon,
this guy.

27:50.886 --> 27:52.366
You know, he's out of control.

27:52.409 --> 27:54.107
You don't know what
he's going to do next.

27:54.150 --> 27:57.588
This guy's swallowing cocaine,
just completely oblivious

27:57.632 --> 28:01.027
to what we're supposed
to be doing, you know?

28:01.070 --> 28:04.987
And I even went so far as
to block the script

28:05.031 --> 28:07.511
while they were partying.
I went through it.

28:07.555 --> 28:11.341
I came up with new ideas,
and it was all for nothing.

28:13.082 --> 28:16.869
I came on to this production
thinking that, uh,

28:16.912 --> 28:19.175
maybe I was going to do
something unique.

28:19.219 --> 28:20.568
It was a reality show.

28:20.611 --> 28:22.788
I guess that's the nature

28:22.831 --> 28:24.659
of this specific production,
anyway.

28:25.660 --> 28:26.922
Thinking about production,

28:26.966 --> 28:31.361
I can sort of compare it

28:31.405 --> 28:35.539
to Orson Welles's last project.

28:35.583 --> 28:37.063
You know, that psychedelic
thing he did,

28:37.106 --> 28:38.368
The Other Side of the Wind.

28:38.412 --> 28:40.153
That's what it reminds me of.

28:40.196 --> 28:44.287
Same type of chaos

28:44.331 --> 28:47.247
and smorgasbord
of actors and characters.

28:47.290 --> 28:49.989
You know, I mean, you get
an idea of what it was like

28:50.032 --> 28:51.991
being in that production.

28:52.034 --> 28:54.558
But you got to
give this guy credit.

28:54.602 --> 28:57.779
This is some interesting stuff,
interesting characters.

29:02.044 --> 29:05.613
Nothing can surprise me
after this.

29:16.885 --> 29:19.453
These Mickey Mouse actor,

29:19.496 --> 29:22.717
let's see who they are,
who they really are.

29:22.761 --> 29:24.284
How are you this morning?

29:24.327 --> 29:25.589
Well, we're having
a little controversy here.

29:25.633 --> 29:27.243
Long night?

29:27.287 --> 29:29.550
You're a little late
for this meeting, aren't you?

29:29.593 --> 29:32.466
I have an idea why you're late.

29:32.509 --> 29:34.860
Yeah? Well, I was working on
the script all night.

29:34.903 --> 29:36.122
Really? A script?

29:36.165 --> 29:37.993
No shit.

29:38.037 --> 29:39.865
You're going to really like
this. I think you guys--

29:39.908 --> 29:42.345
Rinaldo: Well, I know exactly
what you were doing last night,

29:42.389 --> 29:45.653
down here and everything.

29:45.696 --> 29:48.308
Maricon told me.

29:48.351 --> 29:49.962
- I'm the maricon who told him.
- Goran: Are you the maricon?

29:50.005 --> 29:51.659
I hate that name.

29:51.702 --> 29:53.617
I'd rather have Meyer, frankly.
But whatever. Go ahead.

29:53.661 --> 29:55.184
Meyer? Like Meyer Lansky?

29:55.228 --> 29:56.838
Mitch: Meyer Lansky.
I think that's very Spanish.

29:56.882 --> 30:00.624
You know, Mitch told me
how loyal you are to me, man.

30:00.668 --> 30:03.149
You were sleeping with my girl.

30:03.192 --> 30:07.196
So the two girls that were here,
they weren't with you?

30:07.240 --> 30:09.720
Oh, you're pretending not
to know anything about it, eh?

30:09.764 --> 30:12.985
Listen, uh, Don Punta,

30:13.028 --> 30:14.377
I'm really trying my hardest

30:14.421 --> 30:16.031
to stay on board
this production.

30:16.075 --> 30:18.512
I mean, first of all,
the script is horrifying.

30:18.555 --> 30:20.296
Rinaldo: If you only knew
what happened in Miami,

30:20.340 --> 30:22.733
you wouldn't be acting
like these guys, you know?

30:22.777 --> 30:24.300
I got rid of
a couple guys there,

30:24.344 --> 30:26.389
Just like this, all right?
[snapping fingers]

30:26.433 --> 30:29.740
So please, stay with me.
Be loyal to me.

30:29.784 --> 30:32.482
You treat me good,
I treat you better.

30:32.526 --> 30:36.399
I'm going to hire you the
best bitches here for you, man.

30:36.443 --> 30:39.663
You can choose.
And the maricon for you, okay?

30:39.707 --> 30:41.230
Not okay. It's all right.

30:41.274 --> 30:44.494
Rinaldo: So you all going
to be happy, all right?

30:44.538 --> 30:46.540
Is that okay? Clear? All good?

30:46.583 --> 30:47.846
- Okay.
- I like that.

31:01.729 --> 31:04.863
I actually ran into him
at the Nacional.

31:04.906 --> 31:06.865
- Are you serious?
- Yes.

31:06.908 --> 31:08.170
He's at the Nacional?

31:08.214 --> 31:09.432
Well, he was telling me
the place

31:09.476 --> 31:10.999
was a fucking piece-of-shit hole

31:11.043 --> 31:12.696
and he wanted to
get the hell out.

31:12.740 --> 31:14.220
That sounds like Rick.

31:14.263 --> 31:16.613
- It does sound like Rick.
- Wow.

31:16.657 --> 31:20.966
Well, this is my shirt.
This is great.

31:21.009 --> 31:23.272
Okay.
This is a Croatian shirt,

31:23.316 --> 31:24.926
my favourite Croatian shirt.
Okay.

31:24.970 --> 31:27.450
I'm going to try to find him.
He's at this Nacional.

31:27.494 --> 31:32.020
And wouldn't it be wonderful
that I reunite with Rick

31:32.064 --> 31:35.241
and the two of us
will ride off into the sunset

31:35.284 --> 31:39.723
underneath this
great tunnel here in Cuba?

31:56.740 --> 32:01.006
[man singing in Spanish]

32:06.663 --> 32:10.929
The next thing you know,
he's doing all this blow and...

32:15.324 --> 32:17.326
[inhaling]

32:20.373 --> 32:22.375
Oh, fuck.

32:25.944 --> 32:27.815
[inhaling]

32:27.858 --> 32:30.687
Oh, man. [groaning]

32:30.731 --> 32:33.212
I just wanted to,
you know, call you outside.

32:33.255 --> 32:35.083
I want you to keep an eye
on those guys, all right?

32:35.127 --> 32:36.780
I will. I will.
Let's see how they do.

32:36.824 --> 32:39.827
Let's see how this
progresses in preproduction.

32:39.870 --> 32:41.394
- Ah.
- Here you go, buddy.

32:41.437 --> 32:43.396
You read my mind, man.

32:43.439 --> 32:45.354
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Jeez, man.

32:45.398 --> 32:47.008
- It's painful to watch.
- Thank you, man.

32:47.052 --> 32:48.792
I'm starting to sweat
watching you.

32:48.836 --> 32:50.142
A lot of residue here, man.

32:50.185 --> 32:51.708
A lot of shit
is still sticking there.

32:51.752 --> 32:54.581
You know what I mean, eh?

32:54.624 --> 32:56.713
Probably is getting back
in my-- all the way here.

32:56.757 --> 32:58.541
[sniffing]

32:58.585 --> 33:00.413
Can you see any shit here?
No. Really? No?

33:00.456 --> 33:01.675
Goran: There's a little bit
of shit there, yeah.

33:01.718 --> 33:03.764
Really? No. That's maybe...

33:03.807 --> 33:06.375
[blowing nose]

33:06.419 --> 33:10.292
Never seen that, ever,
in any production.

33:10.336 --> 33:12.033
So, I mean, it's the first.

33:12.077 --> 33:13.817
A lot of things
are a first here.

33:13.861 --> 33:17.865
That's nothing, man. I've got
unlimited, you know, supply.

33:17.908 --> 33:20.955
So, you know,
we're all good here.

33:20.999 --> 33:24.045
By the way, Goran,
you have to loosen up, man.

33:24.089 --> 33:27.309
I never see you dance, you know,
participate in the fun here.

33:27.353 --> 33:29.007
I want you to be part
of that fun, too.

33:29.050 --> 33:30.747
You can be too serious.

33:30.791 --> 33:35.100
Hey. Balance, man. Balance.
Fun is part of the business.

33:35.143 --> 33:38.059
And at the end,
I'm going to treat you, man.

33:38.103 --> 33:39.669
I'm going to treat you well,
all right?

33:39.713 --> 33:40.975
Goran: I'd like to see
how we get to that point.

33:41.019 --> 33:42.498
- Okay.
- Goran: But I appreciate it.

33:42.542 --> 33:44.152
- Beautiful, man.
- Goran: Thanks, brother.

33:44.196 --> 33:45.414
I'm counting on you, all right?

33:45.458 --> 33:46.676
- Yeah.
- Rinaldo: I really are.

33:46.720 --> 33:48.156
- Okay.
- Rinaldo: Bye.

33:48.200 --> 33:51.203
[inhaling]

33:53.466 --> 33:57.470
[man singing in Spanish]

34:24.149 --> 34:26.107
Mitch:
This is really strange.

34:44.386 --> 34:46.388
Rick? It can't be Rick. No.

34:52.960 --> 34:56.920
Rick? No. No.
Why aren't you answering me?

34:56.964 --> 34:58.966
Rick. It's not Rick.

35:36.743 --> 35:39.702
[flamenco guitar playing]

35:39.746 --> 35:49.756
♪

37:01.044 --> 37:11.054
♪

37:51.878 --> 37:55.229
Goran: Don Punta, we haven't
even started shooting.

37:55.273 --> 38:00.147
I mean, you're really mocking
that stuff up pretty much.

38:01.888 --> 38:04.238
- You okay?
- I'm perfectly fine.

38:04.282 --> 38:05.761
- Okay.
- Trust me.

38:05.805 --> 38:07.720
Where are these guys, man?

38:07.763 --> 38:09.374
Supposed to be here
for this meeting.

38:09.417 --> 38:11.419
Guys? Hey.

38:13.813 --> 38:15.989
There you are.

38:16.032 --> 38:17.599
Goran:
We thought of this logically.

38:17.643 --> 38:19.732
Like, if we looked at it--

38:19.775 --> 38:21.342
Rinaldo:
Hold on. Hold on.

38:21.386 --> 38:22.822
One thing at a time, all right?

38:22.865 --> 38:25.346
Would you like some stuff
right here?

38:25.390 --> 38:27.087
No, no, no. No, thank you.

38:27.130 --> 38:30.525
